Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_derate_...e_scaling_mode(25.10)  timing_derate_...e_scaling_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_derate_voltage_scaling_mode

Syntax
       timing_derate_voltage_scaling_mode  {first_library  | snap_to_nearest |
       interpolate}

       Default: first_library

       Controls how timing derates are computed when the analysis  voltage  is
       not at the characterization voltage of any of the currently loaded tim-
       ing  libraries.  When the timing analysis environment is configured for
       interpolation, the MMMC library set will contain a list of  timing  li-
       braries at different voltage characterizations points.

       You can specify the following options:

       first_library
              Derates  associated with the first library in the timing library
              list will be used.

       snap_to_nearest
              Allows the software to choose one set of derates  from  the  li-
              brary closest to the required analysis voltage.

       interpolate
              Allows the timer to perform interpolation of the derates associ-
              ated with the two bounding reference libraries.

       Consider the following example:

       create_library_set -name ls_interp_1.50V_1.80V

       -timing [list stdcell_1.50V.lib stdcell_1.75V.lib stdcell_1.80V.lib]

       In this example, by default (first_library) the derates associated with
       the library stdcell_1.50V.lib will be used.

       When set to snap_to_nearest, if the analysis voltage is 1.70V, the der-
       ates from the library stdcell_1p75V.lib will be used.

       When  set to interpolate, if the analysis voltage is 1.60V, then inter-
       polation of derates  from  the  libraries  stdcell_1.50V.lib  and  std-
       cell_1.75V.lib will be used.

       If  interpolation  mode  is selected and the analysis voltage is beyond
       either the smallest or largest voltage, then the library  derates  will
       not  be  interpolated. The derates associated with the nearest bounding
       library will be used. If the analysis voltage is 1.90V, then  only  the
       derates from stdcell_1.80V.lib will be used.

       If  interpolation  mode  is enabled, but not all the bounding libraries
       have derate values, a default derate value of 1.0 will be  assumed  for
       the  missing  derates and used for interpolation. A TA-960 warning mes-
       sage will also be issued.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

